choices.text:
not trying to be what everyone told me to be, but rather trying to find myself in a sea of opinions, suggestions, and confusion. From whom can I learn more, from whom can I better myself, with what intentions stand among you, and whose paths is it that I follow. I contemplate how to find myself as we stand on the Four Paths of Knowledge, “truth/truth alone will conquer the world”. It is truth that I seek, before I go to tinker with other paths of knowledge, physically and spiritually. I am in search of what Buddha told me was right on that winter evening years ago whilst I stood by his side.

I try to put in perspective what Buddha’s words are trying to tell me, which seems to be, “it will be your own calm that will separate you from all of the tumultuous emotions that find us on our walk before death.” In this we must try not to become an aspect of what we try to achieve, whether it is fame, lasting beauty, or rolling in the deep. “In the end there aren’t many ways to foresee who is strong and who isn’t. That is a well kept secret leaving most of the future fateless in their own choices.” Be it celebrities, ‘normal people’, the local dress-up queen at any and every cost. “They all pass away but when the time comes they fear the only thing that really works, staring Death head-on.” He tells me that enlightenment relies on one’s own
